inn1.comm: length ball on off stump, Guptill plays a checked drive towards mid-on
back of a length outside off, a bit of shape away, left alone
fuller now, still a touch wide. Guptill leaves again
full, wide outswinger, another leave from Guptill
aaaand again. Swings fairly early out of the hand, allows Guptill to leave safely
length ball close to off stump, Guptill comes forward and plays a checked drive into the covers

full, angling in sharply towards middle stump and straightening late. Opens up Guptill, who was looking to play through the on side, and beats his edge to hit his front pad. Was missing leg stump, not much of an appeal
angled in again, a touch too sharply, and it slants down the leg side
length ball, fifth-stump line, left alone
full and wide and Guptill drives crisply off the front foot, but straight to Raza at cover
pulls his length back just a touch, and Guptill leaves again
a tiny bit of shape away from outside off. Guptill takes a big stride forward and across and shoulders arms
width again, and this time it's at a driving length. Guptill crashes it away powerfully, flat-batting it into the gap between cover and mid-off
fullish, slanting away from Latham, drawing Latham into a drive away from his body. Wasn't full enough to drive, and the ball took his outside edge and ran away wide of second slip
a touch shorter and closer to off stump, left alone
back of a length outside off, Latham leaves it alone
fuller, fourth-stump line, Latham comes forward and blocks into the off side

full and wide and again he fails to execute a drive as well as he would like. Ends up slicing it, off the outside half of his bat, and it flies uppishly to the right of third man. Panyangara gets a hand to it with the dive, but can't keep it in
length ball angling away from Latham, left alone
drifts onto the pads to start the over, and Guptill clips it away elegantly, into the gap to the left of the square leg fielder
length ball on middle stump, blocked back towards the bowler
full, angling into middle stump, Guptill drives to mid-on
length ball, straightens a touch towards off stump. Guptill, who was initially shaping to play through the on side, adjusts to the movement, lets it come on, and defends into the off side

beauty, and that is gone. Goes wide of the crease, angles it in on a fourth-stump line, and gets it to straighten just a touch. Guptill presses forward and pokes at it, away from his body, and Masakadza accepts the simple, waist-high chance at slip gleefully
length ball, angling in from wide of the crease. Kept Williamson interested, wasn't too far outside off, but he chose to leave it in the end
length ball, curves into the pads, tucks it away to the left of mid-on
full, slants in too far, ends up going down the leg side
fullish, fourth-stump line, nibbles away just a touch. Williamson gets forward, gets his head over the ball, and defends into the off side

length ball on off stump and that is nearly a second wicket in two overs. Williamson defends with soft hands, excessively soft hands almost, and the ball drops down in front of him and bounces backwards, towards the stumps. Doesn't miss off stump by much
similar to the previous delivery. Was just a little wider outside off, and the ball rolls backwards after Williamson defends, but not in an alarming manner
fuller now, on off stump, Williamson plays it with the angle to short midwicket
fullish outside off, left alone, carries through at shoulder height to the keeper
full on middle stump, clipped to the left of mid-on
length ball, fifth-stump line, left alone
once again, teasing away outside off. Williamson is content to leave
fullish, angling in towards off stump. Comes forward and defends with a closed face towards square leg
back of a length, angling in towards off stump, defended off the back foot to mid-on
length ball close to off stump. Williamson comes forward, lets it come on, and defends by the side of his body
full outside off and Latham flows forward to drive, opens his bat face slightly and finds the gap to the right of the diving cover fielder
excellent carry through to Chakabva. Pitches on a good length outside off and he takes it in front of his face after Latham shoulders arms
length ball on off stump, nice line. Stays in the crease and defends into the on side
back of a length, angling away from off stump. Goes back and across and blocks into the covers
back of a length on leg stump, goes back and tucks it carefully to square leg
length ball outside off, left alone
a bit of width outside off, and Williamson goes half-forward and slashes towards cover point
angles this one in too far, and Williamson tickles it off his legs to the fine leg boundary
length ball close to off stump. Williamson defends nice and late, towards backward point
fuller, a bit wider, Williamson lets it go through to the keeper
short and wide, and that is hammered. Gets up nice and tall and crashes it off the back foot through cover point
not that short this time, not that wide, and it's angling in as well, but that doesn't deter Williamson, who rocks onto the back foot and punches it into the gap between cover and mid-off. Super shot
back of a length outside off, punched into the covers
length ball angling across towards off stump. Latham stays on the back foot and punches to mid-on
a bit fuller now, fourth-stump line, Latham leaves it alone
and again, Latham isn't drawn into taking on the angle away from him
Chibhabha strikes, the short ball does it. Latham went for the pull from outside off, but the lack of pace defeated him, and he ended up bottom-edging it into his stumps
back of a length on off stump, blocked back to the bowler
length ball angling into middle stump, goes on the back foot and defends towards short midwicket
back of a length, angling into off stump, defended punchily back to the bowler
fuller now, drifts into the pads, tickles it away to fine leg
excellent delivery, angling in and straightening on a fourth-stump line. Taylor comes forward to defend, ends up playing it off the shoulder of the bat, towards second slip, but with soft hands
length ball angling into off stump, defended to mid-on
length ball on off stump, defended with the angle into the on side
lovely delivery, curving away gently from an off-stump line. Draws Williamson halfway forward to defend and goes past his outside edge
a touch short, a bit of width, punched crisply but too close to the cover fielder, Utseya, who dives to his right to stop that
length ball, nibbles back from outside off to take the inside edge and strike Williamson's pad as he presses forward to defend
back of a length on off stump, gets nicely behind it to defend off the back foot
back of a length outside off, Williamson sees it curving away from him and draws his bat inside the line to leave it
length ball outside off, left alone, and that brings to an end an excellent over from Chibhabha, a maiden
length ball angling into off stump, defended towards midwicket
again, he's clinging on to that off-stump line and the angle in is tucking Taylor up nicely. Defends it into the on side again
a touch straighter now, and that allows Taylor to work it squarer, into the square leg region
back of a length outside off, nips in a little bit to cramp Williamson as he shapes to cut. Ends up dragging it towards cover
length ball on a fourth-stump line, angling in. Williamson pokes it towards point
fuller now, angling into off stump, defended back to the bowler
back of a length outside off. Williamson shuffles across and tucks it quietly towards square leg
full outside off, whipped to midwicket
fullish on off stump and that's a super shot from Taylor. Just leans over the ball and shows it the full face, sends it running away into the gap between the non-striker and mid-on
short and wide, cut away to the right of third man
shuffles across outside off even before the bowler delivers, and punches the back of a length ball to mid-off
length ball angling into off stump, whips it to the right of mid-on
short ball outside off, pulled powerfully but can't beat Williams, who dives to his right to stop it at midwicket
length ball on middle stump, tucked away towards midwicket
back of a length, angles it in too far and Taylor leaves it outside leg stump
full outside off, comes forward and drives back towards the bowler
fullish outside off, presses forward to block it back to Utseya
angles this one into middle stump, defended to midwicket
full on middle stump, whipped to midwicket
back of a length, a bit of movement in towards off stump. Williamson defends into the leg side
length ball angling into off stump. Williamson plays that idiosyncratic defensive shot of his, pressing forward and playing late, almost by his side, and the ball rolls away behind the wicket
back of a length, a touch too straight, tucked off the hips to the right of midwicket
length ball, a bit of width outside off, Taylor plays a checked drive into the covers
shortish, angling into the body, Williamson pulls it down to long leg
length ball close to off stump, comes forward to block it back to the bowler
length ball angling into the pads, tucked away to long leg
gentle length ball outside off, Taylor brings that bottom hand into play, stretching out to paddle that towards long leg
on the pads again, clipped through the midwicket region
back of a length outside off, angling in, whipped to midwicket
a bit fuller and Williamson comes forward to flick to the right of mid-on
there's that paddle-sweep again. Reaches across to take it from outside off and play it down to long leg
slightly wide outside off, Taylor waits for it and steers it down to third man
drifts down leg and it stops on Williamson a touch but he dabs it to square leg
drifts down leg this time a bit too wide and it is called
back of a length on middle, Taylor tries to play it down to third man but is cramped for room
varies the length a bit, goes fuller to Taylor who gets forward and blocks it towards cover
good length on middle and leg, Taylor shuffles across to middle and whips it straight to midwicket
this time he gets it down to third man, waits for the ball to come on and glides it down to third man for one
paddle-swept immediately, fuller outside off, Taylor gets across and sweeps down to fine leg
fired in on middle and ends up a yorker, blocked back to the bowler
slower outside off and Kane gets back and punches but finds cover
slower and fuller from Utseya, driven to cover again
defended off the front foot to short midwicket
Williamson looks to pick his gap on the leg but doesn't get enough of it, ends up swiping the fuller delivery to square leg
a touch of turn immediately, Cremer is a tad short and Williamson rocks back and turns it down to long-on with ease
fuller outside off from Cremer, a bit of turn too, Taylor cuts it well but straight to point
fuller but on off stump, Taylor gets forward and blocks it to cover
advances a couple of steps but doesn't connect, he tries to hit it down to long-on
slower on middle from Cremer this time, Taylor skews it off the outer half of his bat towards cover
what a shot! Fuller and flatter outside off, he picks it up immediately and lofts it without any effort over cover for six
and again! fuller and flatter again and right in KW's arc, waits for it and lofts it beautifully once again, lands just inside the boundary this time. Great batting from Williamson
Utseya tightens his line, goes towards middle, blocked back
fuller and flatter again, beautifully driven again on the ground out to deep cover
slower on middle, Tucked away to midwicket
drifts on leg this time, Taylor whips it but finds midwicket again
well bowled, slower on off stump, Williamson gets forward and defends
well played from Williamson again, slower again on middle, he advances a couple of steps and plays with soft hands towards midwicket, can't find two though
slower but a tad short and wide, Taylor finds point
a touch quicker, slapped back to Cremer off the back foot
he gets a run this time, rocks back on the back foot and turns the shorter ball towards midwicket
skips down the track again and smothers all the spin, easily drilled down to long-on
slides on outside off, Williamson defends off the front foot back to the bowler
a touch wider this time, easily driven to deep cover
a direct hit would have been out! poor calling from Taylor. He waits for the full ball and drives to cover and calls for a suicidal run, a good dive from Raza and picks up and throw
driven down to long-off off the front foot
patted back past Utseya for one, drifted on leg that time
quicker outside off, hit off the front foot to cover again
comes down again and meets the ball as it pitches, drives down to long-on
slow but too wide, driven to cover off the front foot
stays in his crease this time, slow and wide from Cremer again, KW opens the face of the bat and finds the gap through cover
good running this time, slower on off, driven just past cover and long-on is slow on it which allows them to come back for two
quicker outside off, Taylor stays on the backfoot and finds the gap atmidwicket
clips it off the front foot towards long-on, great batting through the middle overs
runs down the track again, meets it as it pitches too and clips down to long-on
shorter, quicker, wider. Taylor cuts but straight to point
nicely slowed up this time, Taylor gets forward and defends
comes out of the crease and clips it well towards square leg
poor ball. Short outside off and wide, easy pickings for KW. Rocks back and pulls it powerfully over short midwicket
even better shot, great stuff, advances a couple of steps and turns it away in the air over midwicket with a discernible use of the wrists
slower and fuller outside off, driven down to long-off off the front foot
short and wide but KW finds point off his cut off the backfoot
great innings, 50 for Williamson, comes down the track and hits it down to long-on
comes on with the arm, Taylor picks it and stays on the back foot, hits it out to cover
quicker again, hits out to point off the front foot
slower on middle, advances down the track and drives it well past the bowler
slower on middle, Williamson turns it off his pads towards square leg
sloppy fielding, slower outside off, Taylor drives it to cover who awkwardly misfields it and allows them the single
back of a length, stays on the back foot and punches it to cover
a bit of turn, waits for it and turns it from outside off to midwicket
slower again, Taylor defends with an angled bat to point
uses his feet this time, gets to the pitch and drives to long-off with no trouble
defended off the front foot, too slow on off but at a good length
a bit more turn, slower at a good length, Taylor prods on the front foot but gets his outer half of the bat and rolls down to third man
use of the wrists again, waits for it to spin and turns the outside off delivery to square leg
picks the gap this time, advances a couple of steps and clips off his pads towards the gap at deep square leg
too slow but too full too, easily driven off the front foot down to long-off
KW tries to find two but cant, races down the track with nimble feet and clips it out to deep midwicket but can't find the gap
short, slow and wide, jumps on the back foot and pulls it easily to deep midwicket
slow, short and on leg this time, Taylor turns it off his pads to short fine leg
lands just in front, short and wide and cut in the air by Taylor but bounces a couple of feet in front of backward point
slower on a fourth stump line, cuts again but on the ground to point
drifts on his pads, and Taylor clips it easily but finds midwicket
can't find the gap again, slower just outside off, Taylor drives off the front foot to cover where a good diving stop prevents the single
uses his feet again and smothers any possible spin, clips down to long-on, awesome stuff from Williamson
short and wide outside off, Taylor rocks back and pulls powerfully to deep midwicket
finds the fielder this time, short and a tad wide again, KW cuts it but straight to point
uses his feet again and tries to loft it over cover but skews it off the inner half down to long-on
slow and outside off, driven to cover
terrible ball, short on leg, easy runs, Taylor stays on the back foot and pulls powerfully to beat the deep square leg
short again on middle, he stays on the back foot and easily pulls it out to midwicket again
a touch fuller this time but it is slow spin, Taylor whips it off his pads to square leg
short and wide and deserves the punishment. Williamson is on the back foot immediately and finds the gap past backward point, not great fielding on the boundary either
superb stuff again, stays on the back foot and whips it off his pads with very soft hands to midwicket
comfortable brace again, shorter on middle and pulls off the front foot this time towards deep midwicket
blocks the full ball on off back to the bowler, probably ran out of air on that last ball
well bowled, tight lines just outside off, good length too, Taylor punches down to long-on off the front foot
advances again a couple of steps but doesn't reach the pitch and adjusts well as he blocks
well bowled again, slower outside off and turn, skewed off to point
awkwardly defended off the front foot back to the bowler. Good lines from Cremer
outside off slightly quicker, punched off the back foot to cover
slightly short on middle, whipped off his pads towards square leg
terrible ball but KW can't capitalise, short and wide and smashed off the back foot but straight to point who fields well
tightens his line immediately, back of a length on off stump, Williamson tries to steer it down to third man but he is cramped for room
drifts on his pads on this occasion and full too, easily clips it between square leg and fine leg for two
on his pads again, hits it well off the front foot but can't beat square leg, a tiny misfield allows them through, good fielding though
a touch wider outside off, Taylor drives it well off the front foot but to cover
decent over, fuller on middle, hits it on the front foot to mid-on
slower outside off, finds cover off the front foot
misses his length and is shorter, pulled powerfully down to deep midwicket
beauty, great stuff from Cremer, slower on middle and turns exaggeratively to beat Taylor's outside edge
slower outside off again, Taylor stays on the back foot but hits it straight to point
turned off the back foot down to long-on
what a shot! beautifully done again. He gets to the pitch of the ball and gives himself ample room and flays it past cover and it runs away for four
fuller and just outside off, good line from Mpofu, patted back to the bowler off the front foot
short and wide on this occasion, Taylor cuts and cuts well too but finds the sweeper cover
great shot again, quietly increasing the run rate with delectable shots like these, full and outside off, KW waits for it and smashes it back past the bowlers head with mid-off in the circle
short and wide again, Kane can find the gap better and hits it to the right of backward point, another comfortable two
slower ball outside off, well played too, waits for it and waits for it some more and glides it down to third man
Taylor repeats the shot, slower ball outside off, steers it down to third man again easily
well bowled from Cremer, slower on middle, defended back to the bowler
wider outside off, smashed off the front foot to cover
slower and fuller, drilled down to long-on
slow and wide, pulled emphatically off the front foot to deep square leg and picks the gap to perfection
slower on middle, turned away off the front foot to square leg
slightly wider outside off from Cremer, Taylor waits for it and whips it off his pads to square leg
tossed up on leg stump, clipped away to deep square leg
down the track and Raza slows it up a bit, shortens his length. Taylor clips to midwicket
sits deep in his crease now, pulls this back-of-a-length ball down to deep square leg
low full-toss on the pads, whipped to deep square leg
sees him coming down the track and floats it wide outside off. Williamson has to reach out to hit the ball, may have been looking to go over cover, ends up slicing it to the third man boundary
short ball down the leg side, and Williamson drags a pull down to the fine leg boundary. Didn't make the greatest contact, but it ran away into the gap to the right of short fine leg
back of a length, angling into off stump, tucked quietly to midwicket
angles this one into the pads, and Taylor works it away to deep square leg

and he's bowled! It was a length ball, angling in from outside off. Unwisely, he tried to dab that down to third man, playing with half a bat, and ended up chopping it onto his stumps. WAIT. HANG ON. Is that a no-ball? It's very close, but there's a tiny sliver of Panyangara's heel behind the line, and Williamson has to trudge back to the dressing room
length ball on off stump and Elliott is a little early into that on-the-up drive. Hangs in the air for a while before bouncing in front of mid-off
fullish, angling into the pads. Looks to flick and inside-edges into his pad, rolls away towards square leg
length ball angling in from outside off. Taylor strides forward and defends into the off side
down the track, doesn't reach the pitch of the slowish ball, clips it into the on side
a bit fuller outside off, driven with the turn to long-on
floated across, outside off, driven to long-off
full on middle and off, clipped to long-on
fullish on the pads, shows the full face and pushes to long-on
a bit quicker on off stump, punched back to the bowler off the front foot
back of a length, turns from middle to off. Taylor goes back and across and works it through midwicket
tossed up on middle stump, Elliott gets his front foot out of the way to drive inside-out to long-off
a bit of flight outside off, defended to extra cover
length ball on middle and off, goes on the back foot and punches it down the ground, to the right of long-on, and brings up his half-century with a double
flighted ball on off stump, dips onto a good length as Taylor comes forward, and he adjusts to defend square on the off side
shortish on off stump, and that's nimble footwork, rocks back, makes room, and slaps to sweeper cover
length ball on off stump, pushed towards midwicket with a straight bat
full, quicker and sliding down leg. Taylor overbalances a touch, but no worries of a stumping, since the keeper fumbles
angled into the pads, tucked away through backward square leg
sees Elliott making room and follows him down the leg side. Whips it to square leg
very full on leg stump, clipped to midwicket
full on middle stump, driven inside-out to long-off
length ball wide of off stump, sliced down to third man with an open bat face
slower ball outside off, sneaks under Taylor's bat as he tries to pull off the front foot
another slower ball outside off. This time he shuffles across and nurdles it away towards deep midwicket

down the track now, gets inside the line but not quite to the pitch of the ball. Swings through the line and lifts it straight and high. Carries far enough, just clears the leaping Raza, running to his left from long-on
slower ball on middle stump, clipped towards midwicket
slower yorker wide outside off, brings his bottom hand into play to jab it down towards mid-off
gentle length ball angling into middle stump, lap-swept to the right of fine leg
full on middle and leg, makes room to drive inside-out to sweeper cover and bring up New Zealand's 200
down the track and that's a brutal hit. Picks up the length ball from outside off and smashes it high over wide long-on with an angled bat, lots of bottom hand
fullish, angling into middle and leg, clipped through square leg
offcutter, wide outside off, and that is easy pickings. Third man is in the circle, and Elliott plays the reverse-sweep, goes very fine and runs away for four. Went off the back of the bat
fullish on middle stump, driven to sweeper cover
shortish, very wide, ends up slinging it beyond the tramline outside off
in the blockhole outside off, uses that bit of width to jab down with an open face and steer it towards deep point
full outside off, driven to long-off

low full-toss outside off, and Taylor was ready for that. He had taken a big step back and across, and was in a nice open position to swing his arms across and give it a big thwack to launch it over midwicket
full and wide, slapped hard to the left of sweeper cover
fullish on off stump, swiped away to deep midwicket
in the blockhole on off stump, clipped down to long-on and that's the 50 partnership. It's come up off 40 balls
full on off stump, clipped away towards wide long-on
back of a length on middle stump. Elliott makes room and punches to sweeper cover
full and wide, driven to extra cover, where bad bounce forces Masakadza to fumble
low full-toss on middle and leg, saw Elliott backing away to make room. Driven down to long-off
low full-toss outside off, driven to long-off
slower ball on middle and leg, makes room and drives inside-out to the left of extra cover
low full-toss on middle stump, and Elliott was in position, back foot deep in the crease and body open at the hips. Swipes it away to the left of the diving short fine leg fielder
yorker outside off, looks to jab it down the ground but can't beat Mpofu, who stretches out his right arm in his follow-through
full and wide, and that is deliberately done, slices hard underneath the ball and sends it flying to the left of the diving short third man fielder
in the blockhole outside off, jabbed back to the bowler
low full-toss wide of off stump, swiped away to deep midwicket
full and wide, and that is superb placement. Flat-bats it hard, beats extra cover diving to his right, and easily beats long-off, sprinting futilely to his left
slower ball, short outside off. Elliott had made himself room, and had to reach out away from his body, and wait and wait before playing a checked pull into the leg side
another short, wide, extremely slow slower ball. Slapped away in the air to sweeper cover
short and wide, slapped away towards sweeper cover
slower full-toss on off stump, clipped down towards long-on, not too much weight on the shot, and the fielder had to run in a fair distance from the rope, allowing an easy second
short outside off, rocks back deep in his crease to cut, Utseya dives to his left at backward point and makes a good stop

slower ball outside off, and for the third time the ball is slapped towards sweeper cover. This time it was hit closer to the fielder, Williams, and they take his arm on again, go for a second, and that was most unwise. The diving Elliott was a fair way from the crease when Chakabva picked up the throw and disturbed the bails
another low full-toss, and that's another monster hit from Taylor. Just takes a big step back and wallops it over wide long-on
full and wide, flat-batted as it deserved to be, rockets into the gap to the left of sweeper cover
wide yorker, a touch too wide, beyond the tramline outside off
better now, yorker close to off stump, dug out back towards the bowler
full and wide again, this time his flat-bat drive goes straight to sweeper cover
slower ball angling into the batsman, rolls off the pad towards the keeper as he looks to work it into the leg side
another slower ball on the pads, tucked away to deep backward square leg
slower ball outside off, swiped down to long-on
full, wide, driven to sweeper cover
high full-toss outside off, around chest height, goes for the big hit and slices it high in the air. It's caught at point by Masakadza, but it's a no-ball
free hit. Wide-ish yorker, jabbed away down to long-off
yorker on off stump, goes for the drive but he can only jam it into the ground, and it bounces up and smacks Panyangara on the chest as he moves to his left to field it
slower short ball outside off, pulled away towards deep square leg
low full-toss outside off, clipped away to deep square leg

full and wide, and that is superb timing from Taylor, the flat-bat drive forces deep point into a sprint to his right and a dive, and he ends up palming the ball past the man coming in from the other direction, from deep extra cover, and that shot has taken Taylor to his 15th ODI hundred and fourth of the year
yorker outside off, jams his bat down on it but can't make contact
full and wide again, sliced in the air over cover
goes for the wide yorker again, beats Taylor as he reaches out to slash, but it's called wide, the ball had gone past the tramline
in the blockhole, closer to off stump this time, jabs it away towards long-off

shot! Sets himself up by going back and across before the bowler released. It was the wide yorker again, but he had changed the length with his initial movement, and had enough leverage to slice it away into the gap between backward point and short third man
again a big back-and-across step, slaps it away into the gap between deep point and deep cover
full-toss outside off, clubbed away down to long-on
slower bouncer outside off, pulled down to deep square leg

full outside off, and that is terrible fielding on the long-on boundary. Ervine runs in to attack the ball after Neesham swipes it in his direction, and ends up fumbling it between his feet and letting it go through to the boundary
full on middle and off, heaves it in the air, on the bounce to long-on
slower ball angled across, fairly short. Barely comes on and he uses his wrists to pull-flick towards deep square leg. Williams chases from deep midwicket and puts in the dive to save the boundary
low full-toss, did well to follow Taylor when he saw him looking to make room. Tries to flick it away but doesn't make contact, and the ball rolls down to the keeper

inn2.comm: full immediately on a fourth stump line, not much swing though, defended off to square leg
a hint of away movement on this occasion, back of a length well outside off, played to cover on his toes
better stride from Masakadza, full and wide and he meets it under his eyes with a good forward block
ooh, nice shot, slightly wide and short from Henry, Masakadza stands tall and punches it though cover and mid-off on the back foot and it races away
wide again on a good length, played into the covers region off the front foot
plays it straighter this time, good looking drive, fuller and driven by Masakadza off the front foot.
too full to start on off stump, not much swing for McClenaghan either, he gets on the front foot and pushed it to the right of mid-off for a brace to begin
quality shot. Too full again, absolutely no seam movement. Chamu gets on the front foot and drills it with a straight bat and it races past mid-off
drifts on his pads this time, Chamu waits for it to come on and clips it to the right of mid-on for an easy single
poor start from McClenaghan. Full and wide and dispatched. Masakadza gets on the front foot and drives it beautifully past the diving short cover
on the pads again, missed opportunity, clips it but straight to short fine leg
big appeal but pitched outside leg stump, improves his line but still not much trouble for the batsman, raps Chamu on the pads but not given
well bowled to start the over, just a hint of seam movement away the batsman from outside off, Chamu shoulders arms
another quality stroke, rides the swing and punches it off the front foot past cover again. A tad full and wide, and drilled. Great timing too
well left this time, a lot more away movement for Henry from outside off, but a bit too wide. Left easily again
a bit shorter this time, he stands tall and guides it point
lucky this time, tries to leave the length ball just outside off, but withdraws his bat just a bit late and it hitst hye inside edge and misses the stumps by not much as it rolls down to fine leg
streaky, in the air, fuller and Chibhabha drives it off the front foot but meets it a bit late and it skews off the outer half and just evades point
bangs it in short this time, well directed, Chamu defends off the back foot with his toes in the air
back of a length again, on a fourth stunp line, well played towards point
beaten for pace this time, good length outside off, he tries to defend but brings his bat down late and gets the toe-end of his bat and rolls away towards point
beaten! Much better over so far. Pushes it across the batsman which beats Chibhabha's half-prod
slightly leg side this time, Chibhabha has enough time to clip it off his hips towards square leg
fuller length and on off stump, blocked off the front foot to cover
away movement again, but too wide. Chibhabha gets a big stride and lets it go
brings it straighter this time, back of a length on middle, Chibhabha is on his toes and clips towards mid-on and they scamper through for a quick single
hurries on to the batsman again, quicker on middle, whipped off his pads towards midwicket off the back foot
poor shot selection this time. It is short and well outside off, Chibhabha tries to pull towards the leg side on the front foot
fifth stump line and fuller, skewed off the inner half of his bat towards midwicket
misdirects his line and drifts down the leg side
and some more poor shot selection. In fact, a repeat of Chamu's earlier in the over. Short and wide. Masakadza tries to smash it over the leg side but misses his pull
just over cover. Pushes it across the batsman again and Chibhabha tries to clip it past midwicket but gets a leading edge which lobs just over short cover
banged in again, doesn't get high enough though. Hamilton has enough time to play it towards square leg off the back foot
better from Chamu. Good stride forward and blocks to mid-on to the full delivery on middle
shorter again on middle, lobs it off the back foot to square leg for another single
better from the openers. Fuller and tries to defend well, gets it off the inner half though and rolls towards square leg
beauty! Pushed across him again but McClenaghan gets his line right, just outside off. Beats Chamu's half-prod once more
what a shot. Delectable on-drive. Overpitched from Henry and Masakadza gets forward and belts it off the front foot past the non-striker.
beats him on the inside edge this time, pulls his length back and cuts him in half
fuller again from Henry, drilled off the front foot to mid-on
good-looking punch, slightly back of a length outside off, hit off the back foot to cover
closer to him and he pulls, bangs it in short again on off stump this time, and Masakadza pulled out to square leg
defended off the front foot with a giant stride towards mid-off
good length delivery on off stump, whipped off his pads towards square leg with ease
nips back in from outside off stump and takes the inside edge, there is a muted appeal however
drifts down the leg stump and Chamu finds no trouble in tucking it off his pads to square leg
smashed on the helmet! Masakadza tries the exotic lap sweep off the front foot, gets down on one knee but the ball is well outside off. Maybe got the edge on to his helmet
more respectful now. Back of a length outside off, defended off the front foot to cover
some more in swing, just a tad outside off but enough to cramp him room as he tries to open the face of the bat and guide it down to third man, he gets too much connection as it finds point
good solid block. Full on off stump, Chamu gets on the front foot and defends well back to the bowler
pulls his length back a touch but the line is similar, blocked back to the bowler again
waits for the bowler to come to him. Henry drifts on middle and it is clipped easily to square leg
bouncer on this occasion, good change up, decently directed too but not enough pace on it as the batsman easily gets under it
slower ball well outside off, Masakadza waits for it and steers it towards third man with a lot more ease this time
good use of the short ball again, maybe trying to induce a pull, Chamu doesn't oblige and ducks under it. Good over nonetheless.
almost gets him, Masakadza gets bat on it just in time. Fuller and a tad of in movement, tucked off to square leg
easily picked off his pads towards deep midwicket
nice drive, no gap though. Full, outside off and driven back to mid-off
waits for the ball to come in with the angle and lets the ball hit the bat and steers it down to third man. Well played, good rotation of strike too
no run there however, good length outside off which is square driven but finds point
straighter line - hitting middle. Skewed off again to square leg
short and wide to start, another missed chance. Belted off the front foot to extra cover
fuller this time outside off, defended off the front foot
straighter on middle, played down to long-on. Not much spin though for McCullum
tossed up and wide outside off, driven to mid-off where they set off immediately, Sodhi picks up and hits the stumps direct but the batsman is in
tossed up again, driven to mid-off again, no gap and no run
nice shot, opens the face of the bat and hits it powerfully to the left of cover. There is a sweeper in position but it was hit extremely well. Good stuff from the openers, just what Zimbabwe needed
lots of turn to start, beautifully landed and plenty of spin extracted. Chamu waits and plays it to the vacant cover region for one
takes the edge this time, flashed hard at it did Masakadza. Just enough connection to take it past slip. Beautiful start from Sodhi
slightly shorter and wide, but plenty of turn again. Hit to cover off the back foot
too full this time, easily smothered and driven down to long-off
turn and lots of it, but a bit short and wide, easily cut away with plenty of time towards sweeper cover
turn again, short and wide again, cut out off the back foot to sweeper cover again
immediate turn, skips down the track but gets the inside half of the bat towards square leg
blocked off the front foot towards midwicket
gets down on one knee and sweeps it, not enough connection though
super shot, at least great shot selection, waits for the ball to turn and lofts it well over mid-off, just enough to get it over him
slower on middle, tucked to midwicket
shorter on off stump, patted back to the bowler awkwardly
tries to hit it against the spin but it rushed on to him, and instead smashes it in the air down to long-off
slower outside off, defended off the front foot to cover
overpitched on this occasion, dug out towards point
slower and shorter but a good line on off stump, punched to cover
quicker and flatter, good variation. Beats him for pace as he tries to cut
slower again well outside off, hit away towards cover on the front foot
slower outside off, gets the outside edge of Chamu's bat, and it races towards third man where a diving fielder can't cut it in
well waited, slower on off stump again, cut well to the right of third man
beautifully tossed up and tries to loft it over cover, but gets some drift and takes the outside edge
well played this time, slightly quicker, he waits on it and opens the face of the bat and guides it down to the third man boundary

gone this time! Huge wicket. Lots of spin from outside off, and spins back in. Chamu gets on the front foot and tries to hit it through cover, doesn't account for the volume of spin and it beats his inside edge and sneaks through to knock back the stumps. Good stand but good timely wicket for NZ too.
slower on off, elegantly driven to mid-on with the turn
excellently landed, pitches on leg or just outside and spins back to off, Masakadza gets on the front foot and blocked
chooses to sweep and connects well, gets down on one knee and hits it well past square leg
slower outside off, hit off the front foot to cover
slower again but just a tad too full, easily drilled down to long-off with the spin
drifts on Ervine's pads, tucked off his pads towards square leg
slower and smashed. He tosses it up and he gets on the front foot and deposits it past the bowler for four. Superb shot.
slower on middle and defended off the front foot
tossed up again, Ervine blocks again with no trouble
tossed up again and there is an appeal, but looks a but leg side, plenty of doubt. Hit him slightly outside leg
slower on middle which is clipped off the front foot to midwicket
sweeps it off the front foot, gets down on one knee, but hits square leg
sweeps again, a bit of an under edge saves him. He gets it down to fine leg for a brace
length ball angling into off stump, punched off the front foot to mid-off
shortish outside off, keeps a little low and sneaks under Ervine's attempted square cut
full now, angling in towards off stump, drives it to the right of mid-off
length ball angling in towards off stump, nice stride forward to defend
back of a length, angling in to middle stump. Stays on top of the bounce and defends into the leg side
slower yorker, gets his line slightly wrong and slants it down the leg side
shortish, angling into off and middle, cramping Masakadza for room. Hops to get on top of the bounce and plays it down into the off side with soft hands
tossed up, angling into middle stump. Presses forward and works it away through square leg
flighted delivery wide of off stump. Masakadza uses the room to try and swing that over the top, ends up dragging it to long on, one  bounce
full on middle stump, driven towards mid-on. Looked to play through mid-off, maybe, and the ball didn't turn as he expected
on the pads, worked into the leg side
nice flight and dip outside off, presses forward, lets it turn, and defends into the off side
flighted ball on middle and leg, and that's cleverly done, reverse-sweeps with precision to the right of short third man
back of a length outside off, looks like the slower one. Waits for it and dabs it towards point
good ball, angled into off and middle and straightened away. Masakadza shaped to play through the on side, adjusted, and steered it down to third man
back of a length, close to off stump, blocked towards short extra cover
slower ball, slips out of his hand and becomes a full-toss outside off. Ervine stands still, lets it come on, and pushes it gently into the covers
short outside off, the angle in cramps Masakadza just a bit, and he has to get on top of some extra bounce too. Chops it down towards point
slower ball, angling into off stump. Lets it come on, looks for the dabbed single to short third man, but the fielder anticipates and cuts it off quickly
length ball, sliding across Ervine. Presses forward to push into the covers and the ball beats his outside edge. Was playing with an angled bat there
length ball angling towards off stump, comes forward and dabs it towards cover
full on leg stump, clipped into the leg side, where Taylor dives left from short midwicket to make the stop
back of a length, stump to stump, punched to mid-on
errs on the short side, and it sits up nicely for Ervine to swat it away, effortlessly, over the square leg boundary
fuller now, close to off stump, comes forward to drive and inside-edges into his front pad
shortish outside off, slower ball, whipped away wristily into the vacant midwicket region
fullish outside off, and he stretches out to drive through the off side. The inward angle forces him to drag it off the inside half of the bat to mid-on
slower bouncer, angling in, ends up looping steeply over the batsman's head and descending rapidly into the keeper's gloves. Called wide for height
length ball angling into off stump, checked drive into the covers, again off the inside half of the bat
angles this into the pads and Masakadza gets on the front foot and works it towards midwicket
inswinging yorker, a touch too straight, clips it off his feet towards deep square leg
full outside off, driven firmly towards mid-off
length ball angling into middle stump, punches it down to long-on and brings up a good, solid half-century. Long way to go still if he wants to take Zimbabwe to victory
on the pads, tucked away to the right of long leg
length ball on off stump, presses forward and blocks into the off side
back of a length outside off, doesn't really come on as he gets on the back foot to punch through the off side, ends up playing it early, down to long-on
back of a length, angling into middle and leg, punched with a straight bat towards deep midwicket
fullish, angling across, presses forward and pushes towards point
flighted ball angled into middle stump, swept with stern majesty down to deep square leg
back of a length, straightens a touch close to off stump. Goes back and across to defend
down the track, and that is powerful. Gets to the pitch, stays inside the line, and hammers it hard between non-striker and mid-off
tossed up on off stump, stretches out and defends towards short midwicket
a bit of flight on middle and off, swept to deep backward square leg
back of a length on off stump, gets on the back foot to defend towards short cover
length ball, a bit of room outside off, eases a drive to the left of sweeper cover
back of a length on off stump, punched down to long-on
fuller now, angling across to middle and off, defended back to the bowler
length ball on middle stump and that is superbly done. Stretches forward and lap-sweeps very fine, times it superbly and it bounces only once before reaching the fine leg boundary
a little too close to force through the off side, off the front foot. Ends up inside-edging into the ground
full on off stump, driven towards mid-off
shortish on off stump, stops on Masakadza a touch, and his pull rolls down to long-on
sharp turn there, pitches on a good length on off stump and smacks into the front pad as he presses half-forward, pops up into the keeper's gloves
down the track now, gets to the pitch to clip towards deep midwicket. Was the googly, but he got right up next to it
on the pads, worked away through square leg
shortish on off stump, makes a bit of room and slaps it to sweeper cover
tossed up on off stump, clips it to long-on
back of a length, angling into off stump, lets it come on and dabs towards point
short outside off, cuts it crisply but straight to point
skips down the track, but the ball comes into him and cramps him for hitting room. Adjusts and defends with soft hands, and the ball rolls back behind the wicket
back of a length on middle and off, tucked away to short midwicket
length ball on off stump and that is awesome power from Masakadza. Takes a step away from the line, and brutalises it down the ground, past the non-striker
yikes. Saw Masakadza move across his stumps premeditatedly and tried to adjust his line. Ended up whanging it a long way down the leg side
back of a length on off stump. Lets it come on, dabs it a short distance into the off side for a quick single
tossed up on middle and off, presses forward and blocks towards point
flighted, too much width, and Masakadza gets down low and hammers that drive over the covers
length ball on middle and off, driven down to long-on
tossed up on middle and off, comes forward and clips to short fine leg
full on middle stump, whipped away to deep square leg
short, and that is such quick footwork. Skips back, opens up at the hips - all of that in the fraction of a second - and pulls with great power to the wide long-on boundary
tossed up on middle stump, clipped down to long-on
flighted full-toss outside off, driven down to long-off
short and wide, slapped away towards sweeper cover
back of a length, turns into the right-hander, who goes on the back foot and works it to deep square leg
full-toss on off stump, checked drive to long-off
gets a little too close to the pitch of this flighted ball, almost yorks himself, drives down to long-off, off the bottom of the bat
short outside off, steered down to third man
short and wide, cracked away to the right of sweeper cover
bouncer, Ervine doesn't have to duck too low to get under it, and the umpire adjudges that it would have gone over his head even if he had just stood still
back of a length outside off, dabbed down towards point
short again, sits up at chest height and Ervine swivels to pull it through backward square leg
back of a length on off stump, defended into the off side
back of a length angling across, and he gets behind the line to defend to short midwicket
back of a length on off stump, punched back towards the bowler
tossed up outside off, driven to long-off
flat, angling into off stump, presses forward to defend back to the bowler
short and wide, slapped away towards sweeper cover
length ball wide of off stump, comes forward and pokes it out towards point
short outside off, stops on Ervine a touch, and he punches it to long-off, bottom hand coming off the handle
length ball, a bit of extra bounce and it straightens a touch outside off. Ervine pokes away from his body and it beats his outside edge
back of a length on off stump, blocked into the off side
back of a length, angling in from wide of the crease, keeps a bit low and Ervine has to jam his bat down quickly to protect his off stump
short and wide and he slashes it away, down to third man
back of a length outside off, dabbed away to third man
angles this into the pads, tucked away nicely through backward square leg to bring up his half-century, seventh in ODIs
tossed up outside off. Masakadza gets on the back foot to punch towards cover
fuller now, brings him forward to block into the off side
flighted ball outside off, too full to reverse-sweep, hits him on the pad but his stride had taken him outside off
tries to come down the track and he quickens his pace and shortens his length, forces him to block it back to the bowler
back of a length outside off stump, punched powerfully to the left of long-off
length ball turning into middle and leg, punched down the ground to long-on
back of a length slower ball outside off, dabbed away towards backward point
down the track and that is a brilliant shot. Skips inside the line and uses his wrists to drill that into the gap between extra cover and mid-off
slower bouncer, loops over the batsman's head as he stops himself after shaping for a hook. Called wide again
slower ball on off stump, presses forward, waits for it to come on, and punches it back to the bowler
shortish outside off, comes in a touch and he gets on his toes to punch into the covers
full on off stump, punched firmly back to the bowler
short, down the leg side, pulled to long leg
slow to start outside off, cut off the back foot where a diving cover stops it from going to the boundary
slower again and driven down to long-on
poor ball and it is banished from his presence. Sliding down leg and he sweeps it easily past the short fine leg for an important boundary
tucked off his pads for an easy single
too slow and too wide, cut away but straight to point

gone this time! what an important wicket. Nathan McCullum strikes again. Tosses it up outside off and it drifts on with the arm and a thin outside edge is taken. Good catch by Ronchi too. What a massive strike just before drinks too.
short on middle, easily driven down to long-on off the back foot.
short and wide, missed opportunity to get off the mark, finds cover with his cut
opens the face of the bat and guides it to sweeper cover with the turn. Well slowed up from Sodhi
drifts on middle and leg and easily tucked off his pads towards deep square leg
good stroke but finds the cover, slower and overpitched and slams it off the front foot
well bowled, beats the outside edge. Chigumbura goes back and tries to cut but a bit of extra turn and bounce goes past the cut
tosses it up but drifts on the pads, easily worked away off his pads for one. Easy singles here for Ervine
fortuitous stroke, tosses it up and well outside off, he tries to come forward and smash it over cover but can only skew it in the air just past point
flighted again on middle and leg, works it off his pads but no run
well swept this time, gets down on one knee and sweeps in the air to the deep square leg boundary where it is well fielded
slower on middle again, patted back to the bowler
flatter and quicker on this occasion, punched back to the bowler off the back foot
tossed up above the batsman's eye line but too full ,ends up as a yorker, Chigumbura digs it out back to the bowler
slower on middle, blocked back off the front foot
some more turn, short and wide and exaggerative spin beats the attempted cut
tossed up but a tad fuller, he opens the face of the bat but guides it to cover
very short and very wide, he leaves it anticipating a wide, but it isn't called
tossed up once more, good bowling, defended out to cover off the back foot. Great over from Sodhi, its a maiden
a bit of tail to start, just a hint of in swing, Ervine gets forward and prods with half-bat and it takes his inside edge and then on to his body
maybe looking for some more in swing and tried a bit too hard on that occasion, drifts down leg
good line, just outside off stump, Ervine gets forward and steers it to point
a bit more tail from McClenaghan. Comes in late and Ervine gets his bat down just in time. Hits it to midwicket
super shot, great shot selection, well played Ervine. Gives himself room and lofts it easily over mid-off and it races away, just when a bit of pressure was being applied
slower ball, good change in pace, it is back of a length outside off, skewed off to cover
high full toss and it is called as a no ball, free hit coming up. Tries for the yorker but ends up  a high full toss on the leg stump, he gets it down to fine leg for one
good change in pace, slower offcutter outside off, Chigs tries to send it over the midwicket boundary but fails to connect.
short and wide to start, loose stuff from Henry. Ervine stands tall and punches off the back foot and found the gap past cover, races to the boundary, excellent timing
fuller length this time, on a fifth stump line, guided to point off the front foot
tighter line still, shifts to a fourth stump line, blocked off the front foot to cover. Zimbabwe biding their time effectively.
worked away off his pads to deep square leg. Good batting from Ervine, picking his shots admirably
back of a length on a fifth stump line again, good ball from Henry, Chigs tries to smash it through cover but finds it instead
just a tad more room and it is enough for Chigumbura to flay his hands at it and find the gap through cover
back of a length and wide too, Chigumbura rocks on the back foot but hits it to point
full on middle, Ervine tickles it with soft hands to deep square leg
good line, top of off stump, steered to point
slower offcutter again outside off, heaved away off the front foot behind deep square leg.
short and wide again, Chigumbura is trying to hit it too hard, gets it down to third man though
tucks the full delivery off his pads to deep square leg
unbelievable shot, maybe the shot of the day, Ervine advances and meets it as it pitches, lofts it excellently with awesome timing and it travels the distance.
tossed up on middle, he defends this time with a straight bat
poor fielding, Ervine gets down on one knee and sweeps it towards short fine leg, McCelnaghan dives and a slight misfield allows them two
worked off his pads again towards square leg
darted in on off stump, Chigumbura drives it to cover
long hop, but it spins away from the batsmen, Chigumbura rocks back quickly and cuts it away to the sweeper. Good over for Zimbabwe
good start, good length just outside the off stump, Chigumbura can't find the gap but can find point
tickled away off his pads with extremely soft hands, well placed too, they sprint back for two. better from Chigumbura
tries to do it again, its on middle and leg and he works it with soft hands but picks out midwicket
speared in the blockhole and squirted out to mid-off. An accurate, swift throw hits the stumps at the non-strikers end and deflects away for an overthrow. Comfortably in was Ervine.
full and wide and smashed over cover, great fielding from Latham at long-off prevents the boundary
low full toss outside off, a thick outside edge has the ball rolling towards third man.
easily swept with quick hands, drifts on leg with a full length, easily paddled to deep square leg
lands just short of sweeper, Chigumbura tries to loft it over cover but again skews it off the outer half of the bat and skies it
what a shot Craig Ervine! He advances down the track and smashes it over midwicket with the spin, superb batting from Ervine. Into the nineties now.
gets the leading edge this time, slower on middle, he tries to work it off his pads
quicker on middle and leg, powerfully swept again to deep midwicket
takes the single this time, short and wide probably anticipating another big shot but Chigumbura stays in his crease and crashes it out to the sweeper
just enough bat on it takes it over long-on, Guptill is a few metres inside the boundary and just clears him. If he had been on the boundary, he would have had a big chance
short on middle, powerfully pulled out to deep square leg
good batting from Ervine, giving the strike to the right-hander, drifts on his pads, tickles it to short midwicket
flatter on off stump, Chigumbura stays on the back foot and finds cover
another vital boundary, moving over for Zimbabwe and Chigumbura, Nathan McCullum goes short on middle again and he smashes it to the vacant midwicket region

gone this time. Tries to clear long-on again but gets nowhere near the boundary. Guptill runs in and takes a good, low catch. He got too close to the ball and couldn't get enough elevation, in fact hardly any at all.
full, quick and on off stump, Williams drives it well but straight back to the bowler
slower offcutter on this occasion outside off stump, squirted off the outside edge down to third man
great ball, full and quick, nothing much Ervine could do with that. He digs it out back to the bowler
low full toss, missed opportunity, he gives himself room and scythes it off the front foot but again straight to point
very slow outside off, swatted back powerfully straight to Neesham. What an over so far.
skips down the track and converts it into a full toss, drilled down to long-on, just one though
wide yorker from McClenaghan, good execution too. Squirted out to the sweeper cover off the front foot
driven powerfully down to mid-off, another dot ball, pressure building, full and quick though. Good ball
slower delivery out of the back of the hand, drilled down to long-on, just another single.
swatted away off the front foot for a much needed boundary to bring up his maiden ODI century, great innings from him. Well deserved too. Slower ball which is dispatched for four over midwicket
full on off stump, gives himself room and tries to clear cover but fails to do so, hits it all along the ground straight to cover.
full yorker speared in just outside off, great execution from McClenaghan. Dug out down to third man.
full and quick on middle, chipped in the air to midwicket but well placed, calls for two immediately and they get it easily
slower delivery out of the back of the hand again, pulled away but deep square leg collects.
oh my word! what a timely stroke, just unbelievable shot selection, gives himself a bit of room and clears his front foot and lofts it over mid-off and goes for six!
slower bouncer down leg side, he gives himself a bit of room and tries to swat it away. No connection though
what placement, excellent timing, slower ball again down leg, gives himself room once more and connects this time however and finds the gap behind deep square leg
very very wide ball down leg, would have been a wide for the right-hander. Pressure on everyone
they'll take em however they can get em. Low full toss on off stump, he swipes at it and gets a thick outside edge and it flies down to the third man boundary.
takes the single, slower ball outside off at a back of a length, worked away to midwicket for one
full and wide, not a bad delivery, Ervine swats it down to long-on for just one
attempts an exotic lap sweep, he keeps one leg on leg stump to prevent it from hitting the stump and it works, hits the pad and rolls away to fine leg, pitched well outside leg
low full toss again, heaved down to long-off in the air with no timing, just enough pace on it to get two though.
amazing, just amazing, drags it from well outside off and sweeps the low full toss to the deep square leg where no one is present. Great shot selection again

and he does it. Almost. What a shot Craig Ervine, an unbelievable innings. Well outside off and he drags it over midwicket with just terrific timing in the air and it travels a few metres over the boundary. Not a bad ball, but when batsmen are striking it as well as Ervine is, there isn't much you can do.

that is it. A wide does it. What a win for Zimbabwe. Just brilliant. Wide and Williams tries to reverse sweep but it is just too wide outside off. A memorable win for Zimbabwe, great display of batting by Zimbabwe and Craig Ervine in particular.
